pageContext.claim: “Through aggressive actions and the devotion of our doctors and nurses, however, we have held our fatality rate far below hard-hit other countries such as Spain and Italy and United Kingdom and Sweden. We're way below other countries.”
pageContext.analysis: The countries named by Trump did have higher death rates at the time, but the United States has been catching up. His comment  goes awry when he suggests the United States is "way below other countries." Among large countries, the United States ranked 9th in the world, far above many of its peers.
